---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { getPublishedPosts } from "../lib/blog";
import { formatDateLong, toISODateString } from "../lib/date";

const posts = await getPublishedPosts();
const blogPostCount = posts.length;
const mostRecentBlogPost = posts[0];
---

<BaseLayout title="Carter | A developer from Utah">
  <style>
    .inline-avatar {
      height: 1lh;
      width: 1lh;
      display: inline-block;
      margin-inline-end: 0.1225rem;
      border-radius: 100%;
      vertical-align: text-bottom;
    }
  </style>
  <section>
    <p>
      <strong>
        <img
          class="inline-avatar"
          src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 64 64'%3E%3Crect width='64' height='64' rx='32' fill='%23d9d9d9'/%3E%3Ccircle cx='32' cy='25' r='11' fill='%23888888'/%3E%3Cpath d='M14 56c2.5-10 9.5-17 18-17s15.5 7 18 17' fill='%23888888'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"
          alt="A headshot of Carter"
        />Carter McBride.
      </strong>
      He's a developer from Utah. Carter considers himself a minimalist. He's written
      a lot of JavaScript. Right now, he works at <strong
        ><img
          class="inline-avatar"
          src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 64 64'%3E%3Crect width='64' height='64' rx='32' fill='%23f03c00'/%3E%3Cpath d='M16 48 28 16h8l12 32h-8l-2.5-8h-11L24 48h-8Zm13-15h6l-3-10-3 10Z' fill='white'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"
          alt="The logo for Adobe"
        />Adobe</strong
      > on the <a href="https://github.com/adobe/alloy">AEP Web SDK,</a> a data collection
      and personalization library that runs on many of the world's biggest websites
      and storefronts.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <p>
      Some of Carter's projects are
      <a href="https://yazzy.carter.works">Yazzy</a> (a webapp to bring reader mode
      to any website),
      <a href="https://carterworks.github.io/rss-reader/">
        his personal RSS reader,
      </a> a small
      <a href="https://github.com/carterworks/substack-to-epub">
        Substack-to-epub scraper
      </a>, and his collection of
      <a href="https://tools.carter.works/"> tools. </a>
    </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <p>
      He can be followed on <a href="https://github.com/carterworks">GitHub,</a>
      <a href="https://mastodon.social/@literallyacar">Mastodon,</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/thatcartermcbride/">LinkedIn</a>, and
      <a href="https://steamcommunity.com/id/CobraLaserFace/home">Steam.</a>
    </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    He has written {blogPostCount}
    <a href="/blog/">blog post{blogPostCount === 1 ? "" : "s"}.</a> The most recent
    was <a href={`/blog/${mostRecentBlogPost.id}/`}
      ><q>{mostRecentBlogPost.data.title}</q></a
    >
    and it was written on <time
      datetime={toISODateString(mostRecentBlogPost.data.pubDate)}
    >
      {formatDateLong(mostRecentBlogPost.data.pubDate)}
    </time>. You can get updates <a href="/blog/feed.xml">via RSS.</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
